New Records: The Jazz went 9-of-42 from 3-point land, which is an uncharacteristic performance and one they aren’t going to put much stock in.
Key Match Events: Cody Williams had his most productive game of the season against the Suns, scoring a season-best 13 points to go with two rebounds and two assists in 22 minutes off the bench.
Pre-Game Insights: There were no pre-game insights mentioned in the article.
Post-Match Reflections: Head coach Will Hardy couldn’t help but think — What if the Jazz played this same game over again? What if his team had played exactly the way they had on Saturday and generated the same shots? They’d probably be more likely to win than lose.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cody Williams had a homecoming game, playing in a familiar gym where he played on the court several times through elementary and high school.
Others: The Jazz have been extremely competitive no matter who the opponent is, though they continue to rack up losses, they have been competitive over the last few weeks.
